items.title: TCS, IBM join hands to deploy India’s largest quantum computer in Andhra Pradesh
items.description: The tech park in Amaravati will host an IBM Quantum System Two installation, carrying a 156-qubit Heron quantum processor, making it the largest quantum computer in India.

items.title: JSW Steel’s 'clean slate' at risk as SC's liquidation order on BPSL jolts industry
items.description: Despite having successfully completed the acquisition and operated the company since 2021, JSW Steel now faces the prospect of unwinding the Rs 19,350 crore deal, raising larger questions about the credibility and finality of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code (IBC) process.

items.title: Covaxin maker Bharat Biotech pivots into cell and gene therapy, eyes cost-effective innovations
items.description: The company wants to use its vaccine-making skills in developing CAR-T and gene therapies at a fraction of the cost, aspiring to be a critical part of the cell and gene therapy value chain, said its Chief Development Officer Raches Ella.
